Lac Minerals Ltd and &lt;Cambior Inc> saidthey completed a second hole at their jointly owned Doyon minein Quebec, which showed two significant gold intersections.    One intersection graded 0.33 ounce gold a short ton over 44feet at depth of 1,411 feet, while the other graded 0.22 ouncegold a ton over 23 feet at 2,064 feet, the companies said. Thehole is 460 feet east of the previously reported first hole.    They said they were now drilling another hole 460 feet tothe west of the first drill hole and expected to report resultsin late March or early April. Reuter&#3;